      title: 'Higher Order Functions in javascript.',
      slug: 'higher-order-functions-in-javascript',
      views: 0,
      description:
        ' # Higher Order Functions in JavaScript\n\nJavaScriptâ€™da funksiyalar oddiygina kod boâ€˜lagi emas, ular **birinchi darajali obyektlar** (â€œfirst-class citizensâ€). Bu degani â€“ funksiyalarni oâ€˜zgaruvchilarga saqlash, boshqa funksiyalarga argument sifatida berish yoki natija sifatida qaytarish mumkin.\n\nShu xususiyat tufayli **Higher Order Functions (HOF)** paydo boâ€˜ladi.\n\n---\n\n## Higher Order Function nima?\n\nðŸ‘‰ **Higher Order Function** â€“ bu:\n\n* Funksiyani **argument sifatida qabul qiladigan** yoki\n* Funksiyani **natija sifatida qaytaradigan** funksiyadir.\n\nOddiy qilib aytganda: **funksiya ichida boshqa funksiyalar bilan ishlasa, u HOF boâ€˜ladi.**\n\n---\n\n## Misol 1: Funksiyani argument sifatida berish\n\n```javascript\nfunction greet(name) {\n  return `Hello, ${name}!`\n}\n\nfunction processUserInput(callback) {\n  const name = "Asilbek"\n  return callback(name)\n}\n\nconsole.log(processUserInput(greet)) \n// Output: Hello, Asilbek!\n```\n\nBu yerda `processUserInput` â€“ **Higher Order Function**, chunki u boshqa funksiyani (`greet`) argument sifatida olmoqda.\n\n---\n\n## Misol 2: Funksiyani qaytarish\n\n```javascript\nfunction multiplier(factor) {\n  return function (number) {\n    return number * factor\n  }\n}\n\nconst double = multiplier(2)\nconsole.log(double(5)) // 10\n```\n\nðŸ‘‰ `multiplier` â€“ HOF, chunki u boshqa funksiya qaytaradi.\n\n---\n\n## Amaliy Higher Order Functions:\n\nJavaScriptâ€™da koâ€˜p ishlatiladigan array metodlari aslida **HOF** hisoblanadi:\n\n### `map()`\n\n```javascript\nconst numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4]\nconst doubled = numbers.map(num => num * 2)\nconsole.log(doubled) // [2, 4, 6, 8]\n```\n\n### `filter()`\n\n```javascript\nconst numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\nconst even = numbers.filter(num => num % 2 === 0)\nconsole.log(even) // [2, 4]\n```\n\n### `reduce()`\n\n```javascript\nconst numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4]\nconst sum = numbers.reduce((acc, num) => acc + num, 0)\nconsole.log(sum) // 10\n```\n\n---\n\n## Nega Higher Order Functions muhim?\n\n* **Kod qayta ishlatiladi** (reusable code).\n* **Chiroyli va ixcham yoziladi**.\n* **Functional programming** uslubini qoâ€˜llash imkonini beradi.\n\n---\n\n## Xulosa\n\nHigher Order Functions â€“ JavaScriptâ€™ni kuchli qiladigan asosiy konsepsiyalardan biri. `map`, `filter`, `reduce` kabi metodlar orqali ularni kundalik kodlashda ishlatamiz. Ular yordamida **kod soddaroq, moslashuvchan va tushunarli** boâ€˜ladi. ',
