      slug: 'understanding-promises-in-javascript-a-comprehensive-guide',
      views: 0,
      description:
        ' # Understanding Promises in JavaScript: A Comprehensive Guide\n\nJavaScriptâ€™da **asynchronous** vazifalarni bajarishda koâ€˜p ishlatiladigan konseptlardan biri â€“ bu **Promise**.\n\nPromise â€“ bu kelajakda **natija qaytarishi mumkin boâ€˜lgan operatsiyani** ifodalaydi: muvaffaqiyatli boâ€˜lsa qiymat qaytaradi, xatolik boâ€˜lsa esa error.\n\n---\n\n## Promise nima?\n\nðŸ‘‰ Promise â€“ bu obyekt boâ€˜lib, u 3 ta holatdan birida boâ€˜lishi mumkin:\n\n1. **Pending** â€“ kutilmoqda (hali natija yoâ€˜q).\n2. **Fulfilled** â€“ muvaffaqiyatli bajarildi (`resolve`).\n3. **Rejected** â€“ xatolik yuz berdi (`reject`).\n\n---\n\n## Oddiy Promise misoli\n\n```javascript\nconst myPromise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n  let success = true\n\n  if (success) {\n    resolve("âœ… Data received!")\n  } else {\n    reject("âŒ Something went wrong.")\n  }\n})\n\nmyPromise\n  .then(result => console.log(result)) \n  .catch(error => console.error(error))\n```\n\n---\n\n## `then()`, `catch()`, va `finally()`\n\n* **then()** â†’ muvaffaqiyatli natija qaytarsa ishlaydi.\n* **catch()** â†’ xatolik boâ€˜lsa ishlaydi.\n* **finally()** â†’ natijadan qatâ€™i nazar ishlaydi.\n\n```javascript\nfetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1")\n  .then(response => response.json())\n  .then(data => console.log(data))\n  .catch(err => console.error("Error:", err))\n  .finally(() => console.log("Request finished"))\n```\n\n---\n\n## Promise Chaining\n\nBir nechta `then()` larni ketma-ket ulash mumkin:\n\n```javascript\nnew Promise(resolve => resolve(2))\n  .then(num => num * 2)   // 4\n  .then(num => num * 3)   // 12\n  .then(num => console.log(num)) // 12\n```\n\n---\n\n## `Promise.all()`\n\nBir nechta promise parallel bajarilishi uchun ishlatiladi.\n\n```javascript\nconst p1 = Promise.resolve("Hello")\nconst p2 = Promise.resolve("World")\n\nPromise.all([p1, p2]).then(values => {\n  console.log(values) // ["Hello", "World"]\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## `Promise.race()`\n\nFaqat eng birinchi bajarilgan promise qaytariladi.\n\n```javascript\nconst p1 = new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(() => resolve("One"), 2000))\nconst p2 = new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(() => resolve("Two"), 1000))\n\nPromise.race([p1, p2]).then(value => console.log(value)) \n// Output: "Two"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Async/Await bilan Promises\n\n`async/await` â€“ bu Promiseni yanada **tushunarli va toza sintaksis** bilan yozish usuli.\n\n```javascript\nasync function getData() {\n  try {\n    const response = await fetch("https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts/1")\n    const data = await response.json()\n    console.log(data)\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error("Error:", error)\n  } finally {\n    console.log("Request finished")\n  }\n}\n\ngetData()\n```\n\n---\n\n## Xulosa\n\n* Promise â€“ **asynchronous vazifalarni boshqarish** uchun juda qulay vosita.\n* `then`, `catch`, `finally` â€“ natijani boshqarishda ishlatiladi.\n* `Promise.all`, `Promise.race` â€“ parallel vazifalar uchun.\n* `async/await` â€“ Promiseni soddalashtiradi va kodni oâ€˜qishni osonlashtiradi. ',
